{
  "stem": "25639.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "While I was in the camp, I think all of us found it easier to socialize-- the very limited way that we socialized-- with people who spoke our languages.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Most of us spoke several languages.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, you see, the-- the hunger and the long work days put us in such physical condition that we had no incentive to make new friends.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Secondly, it really was discouraged by the [? blockalteste. ?] That means the eldest of the block.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] She wasn't really the eldest, but she was picked by the SS to do this job-- to keep an eye on us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So we usually tried to converse with those of us who were family members, or from our-- those who came from our town, or those who spoke our languages.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I think that's-- that had to be simple.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "This became a little different when I moved onto another camp, and another camp, and so on, until I went through seven camps.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "When I no longer had my mother, and sister, and my first cousins, a few first cousins who were with me in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Then, I, being the sociable person that I am, I had the need for human warmth, and love, and-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I always made friends.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[SOBS] This girl who gave me her overcoat came from not-- less than 20 miles from our hometown.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she even knew about our family.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] She thought we were even related.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was really incredible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She was in several camps with me, and then I-- sort of, my memory-- I can't remember what happened to us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But eventually, in the end, we were liberated together.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
